node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/01-metadata/app-icons.md:> - By default, generated icons are [**statically optimized**](/docs/app/glossary#prerendering) (generated at build time and cached) unless they use [Request-time APIs](/docs/app/glossary#request-time-apis) or uncached data.
node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/01-metadata/app-icons.md:> - You can generate multiple icons in the same file using [`generateImageMetadata`](/docs/app/api-reference/functions/generate-image-metadata).
node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/01-metadata/app-icons.md:> - App icons are special Route Handlers that are cached by default unless they use a [Request-time API](/docs/app/glossary#request-time-apis) or [dynamic config](/docs/app/guides/caching-without-cache-components#dynamic) option.
node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/01-metadata/app-icons.md:A promise that resolves to an object containing the [dynamic route parameters](/docs/app/api-reference/file-conventions/dynamic-routes) object from the root segment down to the segment `icon` or `apple-icon` is colocated in.
node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/01-metadata/app-icons.md:> **Good to know**: If you use [`generateImageMetadata`](/docs/app/api-reference/functions/generate-image-metadata), the function will also receive an `id` prop that is a promise resolving to the `id` value from one of the items returned by `generateImageMetadata`.
